249
00:30:49.314 --> 00:30:51.806
Someone will move
against the Salamancas.

250
00:30:53.485 --> 00:30:55.954
Which brings war.

251
00:30:57.389 --> 00:31:00.382
Which brings chaos.

252
00:31:02.027 --> 00:31:03.518
Which brings...

253
00:31:04.329 --> 00:31:05.820
the D.E.A.

254
00:33:06.852 --> 00:33:08.252
What's up?

255
00:33:08.420 --> 00:33:10.753
It's busted again.

256
00:33:19.364 --> 00:33:21.230
It's just the chain.

257
00:33:21.533 --> 00:33:24.298
Want me to do it or you
wanna try it yourself?

258
00:33:26.838 --> 00:33:28.329
Okay.

259
00:33:29.241 --> 00:33:31.972
This is the last time. so watch.

260
00:33:32.878 --> 00:33:34.471
All right.

261
00:33:34.646 --> 00:33:38.947
So you take this. give it a
little play. right about there.

262
00:33:39.384 --> 00:33:42.183
Loop it around
the big gear. yeah?

263
00:33:42.354 --> 00:33:43.947
And then...

264
00:33:45.624 --> 00:33:47.786
- That's all there is to it.
- Okay.

265
00:33:51.196 --> 00:33:53.791
- And?
- Thanks. Dad.

266
00:33:58.003 --> 00:34:00.632
Make sure Mom
knows where you are.

267
00:34:43.682 --> 00:34:45.548
Hi. Denise.

268
00:34:46.451 --> 00:34:48.420
Uh. yeah. it's Barry.

269
00:34:48.587 --> 00:34:52.524
Uh. listen. could you let Mr. Eglin
know I'm gonna be late this morning?

270
00:34:53.358 --> 00:34:55.691
I might miss the staff meeting.

271
00:34:57.529 --> 00:35:01.022
No. no. Car troubles.
Probably just a dead battery.

272
00:35:01.399 --> 00:35:04.198
Yeah. I know. I know.

273
00:35:04.369 --> 00:35:06.463
Practically brand-new.

274
00:35:06.905 --> 00:35:08.965
Okay. thanks.

275
00:36:11.603 --> 00:36:14.539
Bruce had the speed. He could
kick you before you saw him move.

276
00:36:14.706 --> 00:36:17.972
- You ever watched a Liston fight?
- We're talking about what?

277
00:36:18.143 --> 00:36:21.841
- Boxing? That's something else.
- No. we're talking a street fight.

278
00:36:22.013 --> 00:36:25.745
- Street fight? Great. so Bruce can kick.
- We're not talking a movie fight.

279
00:36:25.917 --> 00:36:29.615
- We're talking about weight. about reach.
- Boxing is a sport.

280
00:36:29.788 --> 00:36:31.689
Martial arts is life and death.

281
00:36:31.856 --> 00:36:34.018
Look. I don't care
how fast you are.

282
00:36:34.192 --> 00:36:37.060
Muhammad Ali hits you.
you're going down. that's a fact.

283
00:36:37.228 --> 00:36:39.254
If he hits you.

284
00:36:39.431 --> 00:36:42.526
Bruce Lee. he knows the anatomy.

285
00:36:42.701 --> 00:36:44.863
He's got the moves. He's
gonna find an opening.

286
00:36:45.036 --> 00:36:47.528
Without power. the
opening doesn't mean squat.

287
00:36:47.706 --> 00:36:50.801
- How much does he weigh? MAN
1: I don't know. Maybe a buck-thirty.

288
00:36:50.975 --> 00:36:55.071
Ali was the heavyweight champ.
He's got 100 pounds on Lee.

289
00:36:55.246 --> 00:36:57.078
Bruce feints for Ali's head.

290
00:36:57.248 --> 00:37:00.912
But he goes low and sweeps him
to the deck. Ali goes down hard.

291
00:37:01.086 --> 00:37:02.384
It's all over.

292
00:37:02.554 --> 00:37:04.318
Does he have a gun?

293
00:37:04.489 --> 00:37:07.891
- I'm sorry?
- Does Bruce Lee have a gun?

294
00:37:08.059 --> 00:37:11.188
If he doesn't. it's Ali in
three minutes or less.

295
00:37:11.696 --> 00:37:14.723
See? That's what I'm
saying. That's what I'm say...

296
00:37:15.133 --> 00:37:17.728
Hey. hold on. Wait. wait.

297
00:37:20.205 --> 00:37:23.175
Did you sign. uh.
Tina's birthday card?

298
00:37:23.341 --> 00:37:25.503
- No.
- Would you mind?

299
00:37:26.611 --> 00:37:28.580
Not at all.

300
00:37:33.752 --> 00:37:36.586
You're out of line.
- I'm saying...

301
00:37:36.755 --> 00:37:39.953
if Lee tried to sweep
Ali's legs. he'll sidestep.

302
00:37:40.125 --> 00:37:42.617
Ali was fast for his size. yes.

303
00:37:42.794 --> 00:37:45.628
But if he gets hit with a low
kick. he won't know what to do.

304
00:37:45.797 --> 00:37:48.130
I know what he'll
do. He'll do just fine.

305
00:37:48.299 --> 00:37:49.597
You're nuts.

306
00:37:49.768 --> 00:37:51.634
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

307
00:37:51.803 --> 00:37:54.534
Bruce was a brawler.
okay? He gets in quick...

308
00:40:14.345 --> 00:40:15.472
I got it.

309
00:40:15.647 --> 00:40:17.206
Uh. yeah?

310
00:40:18.082 --> 00:40:20.210
Ramirez. team leader.

311
00:40:20.385 --> 00:40:21.512
Yes. sir.

312
00:40:21.686 --> 00:40:24.019
Ramirez. what do
you think you're up to?

313
00:40:24.489 --> 00:40:27.288
We're just pulling an
order. Something wrong?

314
00:40:27.458 --> 00:40:30.587
May I ask why none of your
guys are wearing a lift belt?

315
00:40:31.729 --> 00:40:33.254
Lift belt?

316
00:40:33.431 --> 00:40:35.559
- We don't usually...
- Stop what you're doing.

317
00:40:35.733 --> 00:40:39.363
Go to the equipment room.
You get lift belts and gloves.

318
00:40:39.537 --> 00:40:42.871
You use them. Rules
are rules. got me?

319
00:40:43.041 --> 00:40:44.304
Sure. Sure. Okay.

320
00:40:44.475 --> 00:40:46.307
On the double.

321
00:40:46.477 --> 00:40:49.504
Hey. hold up. Shut it down.

322
00:40:49.681 --> 00:40:51.479
Shut it down.

323
00:41:12.337 --> 00:41:13.828
Uh. excuse me.

324
00:41:14.005 --> 00:41:15.735
I think this belongs to you.

325
00:41:16.908 --> 00:41:19.810
Oh. my God. Ha. ha.

326
00:41:20.211 --> 00:41:22.976
Thank you. Where
did you find it?

327
00:41:23.648 --> 00:41:25.480
I need to talk to your manager.

328
00:41:27.018 --> 00:41:29.954
I waltz through security
with someone else's ID.

329
00:41:30.121 --> 00:41:32.147
Nobody gives me a second look.

330
00:41:32.724 --> 00:41:37.287
When the rightful owner shows up.
there's no facility-wide badge check.

331
00:41:37.462 --> 00:41:40.489
I find access doors left
unlocked or propped open.

332
00:41:40.665 --> 00:41:42.793
Passwords written
on Post-it notes.

333
00:41:42.967 --> 00:41:47.428
Warehouse workers are using pen
and paper instead of electronic devices...

334
00:41:47.605 --> 00:41:49.870
which leaves you
open to pilfering.

335
00:41:50.041 --> 00:41:52.533
You got duplicate
routing numbers on cargo.

336
00:41:52.710 --> 00:41:57.375
Surveillance camera blind spots on
the north and the east side of the floor.

337
00:41:57.548 --> 00:42:01.610
Inventory documents going into
the trash instead of being shredded.

338
00:42:01.786 --> 00:42:06.349
Not to mention loading equipment
driven at unsafe speeds...

339
00:42:06.524 --> 00:42:07.719
- Wait. Wait.
- And crews...

340
00:42:07.892 --> 00:42:11.488
- Wait. hold on. Who are you exactly?
- Disregarding safe...

341
00:42:11.996 --> 00:42:13.624
Ehrmantraut.

342
00:42:13.798 --> 00:42:15.528
Security consultant.

343
00:42:17.168 --> 00:42:20.468
Well. all due respect. I don't know
anything about a security consultant.

344
00:42:20.638 --> 00:42:22.630
Well. you wouldn't. would you?

345
00:42:23.307 --> 00:42:25.833
Maybe you'd best call corporate.

346
00:42:26.010 --> 00:42:29.708
Try Lydia Rodarte-Quayle.

347
00:42:48.433 --> 00:42:50.425
I'm truly sorry. Jimmy.

348
00:42:50.601 --> 00:42:52.661
Thank you. Cliff.
I appreciate that.

349
00:42:55.373 --> 00:42:56.534
Hey.

350
00:42:56.707 --> 00:42:58.335
He was a hell of a lawyer.

351
00:42:58.509 --> 00:42:59.670
Yes. he was.

352
00:43:02.513 --> 00:43:04.004
Jimmy.

353
00:43:04.615 --> 00:43:07.517
We're gonna miss him so much.

354
00:43:07.685 --> 00:43:09.017
Thank you. Brenda.

355
00:43:12.056 --> 00:43:14.753
- I'm sorry for your loss.
- Thanks. Brian.

356
00:43:18.863 --> 00:43:20.593
Jimmy. I'm so sorry.

357
00:43:20.765 --> 00:43:23.325
Oh. thanks. Appreciate that.

358
00:43:48.559 --> 00:43:50.255
<i>Thank you.</i>

359
00:44:28.533 --> 00:44:31.901
I think I owe you the
truth about Chuck.

360
00:44:33.171 --> 00:44:34.935
Those lanterns.

361
00:44:36.474 --> 00:44:40.104
He was living in that house
without electricity for two years.

362
00:44:40.278 --> 00:44:42.747
He knew how to
use those lanterns.

363
00:44:42.914 --> 00:44:47.545
He was careful. I saw it. I know you
did too. There was never a problem.

364
00:44:49.420 --> 00:44:51.821
I know it's a
terrible thing to...

365
00:44:55.059 --> 00:44:57.654
I don't think what
happened was an accident.

366
00:45:07.772 --> 00:45:12.506
You probably heard Chuck
was retiring from HHM.

367
00:45:13.277 --> 00:45:15.337
But that's not the truth.

368
00:45:16.714 --> 00:45:21.175
The truth is that we
had a disagreement...

369
00:45:21.352 --> 00:45:23.287
and I pushed him out.

370
00:45:23.788 --> 00:45:24.812
I made him go.

371
00:45:24.989 --> 00:45:28.426
Chuck was sick for years.
And after the bar hearing...

372
00:45:28.593 --> 00:45:30.960
The bar hearing had
nothing to do with it.

373
00:45:31.762 --> 00:45:33.321
Okay.

374
00:45:33.497 --> 00:45:36.661
The fact is. he started
getting better after that.

375
00:45:37.535 --> 00:45:41.768
He took more of an interest in the firm.
He came to work. We left the lights on.

376
00:45:42.206 --> 00:45:46.906
He was improving until the thing with
the insurance. it wasn't the bar hearing.

377
00:45:48.079 --> 00:45:49.945
The insurance?

378
00:45:50.448 --> 00:45:52.917
It was a ridiculous thing.

379
00:45:55.052 --> 00:45:56.577
I should've just let it go.

380
00:45:56.754 --> 00:45:59.417
I mean. God knows
he's done enough for me.

381
00:45:59.790 --> 00:46:02.885
But he kept pushing and I. um...

382
00:46:03.227 --> 00:46:05.321
I got my back up.

383
00:46:05.930 --> 00:46:07.899
What about the insurance?

384
00:46:08.065 --> 00:46:10.864
It was. uh. our
malpractice insurance.

385
00:46:11.035 --> 00:46:14.164
They found out about Chuck's
condition. raised our rates.

386
00:46:14.772 --> 00:46:18.231
Chuck went ballistic.
He wanted to go to war.

387
00:46:18.409 --> 00:46:20.139
I drew a line.

388
00:46:20.311 --> 00:46:22.303
He wouldn't back down.

389
00:46:22.480 --> 00:46:23.641
So I forced him out.

390
00:46:29.587 --> 00:46:32.455
It never occurred to
me that I could hurt him.

391
00:46:33.391 --> 00:46:35.860
He always seemed so strong.

392
00:46:36.427 --> 00:46:38.157
But he wasn't.

393
00:46:39.630 --> 00:46:42.566
I think he did what
he did because of me.

394
00:46:50.274 --> 00:46:53.267
Well. Howard. I guess
that's your cross to bear.

395
00:47:12.797 --> 00:47:14.663
Look at her go.

396
00:47:16.267 --> 00:47:19.760
So I'm gonna make
coffee. Anybody want some?
